COVID Forecast Evaluation

Dependencies & Libraries

Specifying the parameters of the evalcast::get_predictions function

# 50 dates from "2020-07-20" to "2021-06-28" spaced 1 week apart
our_pred_dates <- get_covidhub_forecast_dates("CMU-TimeSeries")
n_dates <- length(our_pred_dates)


# Parameters of the evalcast::get_predictions function
forecast_dates <- our_pred_dates[n_dates - 1 * 7:4]
forecaster <- larrys_anteater # change the forecaster for county level
forecaster_name  <- "larry's anteater"

forecaster_signals <- dplyr::tibble(
  data_source = "jhu-csse",
  signal = c("deaths_incidence_num",
             "confirmed_incidence_num"),
  start_day = lubridate::ymd("2021-01-01"),
  geo_type = "state"
)


aheads  <- 1:4
lags <- c(0, 7, 14)
forecaster_args <- list(
  ahead = aheads,
  lags = lags,
  tau = evalcast::covidhub_probs(), # 23 quantiles
  training_window_size = 90,
  featurize = animalia::make_7dav_featurizer()
)

Get the predictions for our forecaster (you can leave this call as-is, unless you want to change incidence_period):

# Downloading signal data from the start date up until the first forecast date
# The data is retrieved in batches based on the number of forecast dates (i.e., from the start date up to a forecast date)

set.seed(1)  # for reproducibility as corrections have randomness
predictions <- evalcast::get_predictions(
  forecaster = forecaster,
  name_of_forecaster = forecaster_name,
  signals = forecaster_signals,
  forecast_dates = forecast_dates,
  incidence_period = "epiweek",
  #apply_corrections = state_corrector,
  forecaster_args = forecaster_args
)


# Why the predictions data don't have the confirmed_incidence_number signal?
# Replacing negative predictions with 0
predictions$value <- pmax(predictions$value, 0)

Retrieving forecasts from other competitors

Get the competition and evaluate the predictions on the error metrics:

# For forecasts at the state level:
competition <- c("COVIDhub-ensemble", "COVIDhub-baseline",
                 "CMU-TimeSeries", "Karlen-pypm")

submitted <- lapply(competition[1:3], get_covidhub_predictions, 
                    forecast_dates = forecast_dates, 
                    signal = "deaths_incidence_num")

submitted[[4]] <- get_covidhub_predictions(
  "Karlen-pypm", 
  forecast_dates = forecast_dates - 1,
  signal = "deaths_incidence_num") %>%
  mutate(forecast_date = forecast_date + 1)
# For forecasts at the county level:
#competition <- c("COVIDhub-ensemble",

submitted <- bind_rows(submitted) %>% filter(ahead < 5)
all_predictions <- bind_rows(predictions, submitted)

Evaluating the predictions

# For county prediction, set geo_type = "county"
results <- evaluate_covid_predictions(
  all_predictions,
  backfill_buffer = 0,
  geo_type = "state") %>% intersect_averagers(c("forecaster"), c("forecast_date", "geo_value"))

Comparing forecasters

results %>% group_by(forecast_date) %>% summarise(n_distinct(geo_value))
## # A tibble: 4 x 2

subtitle = sprintf("Forecasts made over %s to %s",
                   format(min(forecast_dates), "%B %d, %Y"),
                   format(max(forecast_dates), "%B %d, %Y"))

plot_canonical(results, x = "ahead", y = "ae", aggr = mean) +
  labs(subtitle = subtitle, xlab = "Weeks ahead", ylab = "Mean AE") +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom") + 
  scale_y_log10()

plot_canonical(results, x = "ahead", y = "wis", aggr = mean) +
  labs(subtitle = subtitle, xlab = "Weeks ahead", ylab = "Mean WIS") +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom") + 
  scale_y_log10()

plot_canonical(results, x = "ahead", y = "coverage_80", aggr = mean) +
  labs(subtitle = subtitle, xlab = "Weeks ahead", ylab = "Mean Coverage") +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom") + 
  coord_cartesian(ylim=c(0,1)) + geom_hline(yintercept = .8, color="black")

library(stringr)
library(bsselectR)

states <- as.character(sort(unique(results$geo_value)))

plots <- lapply(states, function(x) {
  state = filter(results, geo_value == x)
  p <- plot_canonical(state, x = "ahead", y = "ae", aggr = mean)
  p
})

paths <- paste0(states, ".png")
pwalk(list(paths, plots), ggsave, path = "plots")
state_plots <- paste0(list.files("plots", full.names = TRUE))
names(state_plots) <- str_replace_all(state_plots, c("\\.png" = "", "plots/" = ""))
bsselect(state_plots, type = "img", selected = "ak",live_search = TRUE, show_tick = TRUE)
